results.name: Expansion of q^(-5/6) * (eta(q) * eta(q^6)^2 / eta(q^3))^2 in powers of q.
link: G. C. Greubel, Table of n, a(n) for n = 0..2500
mathematica: a[ n_] := SeriesCoefficient[ (QPochhammer[ x] QPochhammer[ x^6]^2 / QPochhammer[ x^3])^2, {x, 0, n}];
program: (PARI) {a(n) = my(A); if( n<0, 0, A = x * O(x^n); polcoeff( (eta(x + A) * eta(x^6 + A)^2 / eta(x^3 + A))^2, n))};

(PARI) {a(n) = my(A, p, e, x, y, a0, a1); if( n<0, 0, n = 6*n + 5; A = factor(n); -1/2 * prod( k=1, matsize(A)[1], [p, e] = A[k,]; if( p==2, 0, p==3, (-1)^e, a0 = 1; a1 = y = -sum( x=0, p-1, kronecker( x^3 - x^2 - 4*x + 4, p)); for( i=2, e, x = y*a1 - p*a0; a0 = a1; a1 = x); a1)))};
results.author: _Michael Somos_, May 19 2015
